# av11n versification — the CANONICAL base (KJV/English numbering, ADR-0010).
#
# The corpus canonical numbering IS av11n, so an av11n translation diverges from
# canonical NOWHERE: this file intentionally carries zero mapping lines and its
# versification_map is empty (the sparse table's identity case). Both bundled
# translations (KJV, BSB) declare `versification: av11n`, so neither populates a
# single row — correct, and exactly the OVERVIEW §5 gap the divergent test
# fixture (scripts/ingest/fixtures/divergent.vrs) exists to exercise instead.
#
# Adding a translation on a DIFFERENT scheme (e.g. a Hebrew/org-numbered
# edition) = dropping its `<scheme>.vrs` here with `NATIVE = CANONICAL` mapping
# lines; run.ts resolves the file by the translation's `versification` field and
# parseVrs() (vrs.ts) turns it into rows.
